## API Conventions

- **Base URL**: `/api/v1`
- **Format**: JSON
- **Auth**: JWT Bearer token
- **Errors**: RFC 7807 Problem Details
- **Pagination**: `?page=1&pageSize=20`
- **Sorting**: `?sortBy=name&sortOrder=asc`
- **Filtering**: `?status=active&search=xyz`

### Response Format
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "data": { ... },
  "errors": null
}
```

---

## Database Conventions

### Naming
- **Tables**: `snake_case` (e.g., `fuel_types`, `meter_readings`)
- **Primary Keys**: `id` (UUID, `gen_random_uuid()`)
- **Foreign Keys**: `{entity}_id` (e.g., `station_id`, `tank_id`)
- **Timestamps**: `created_at`, `updated_at` (TIMESTAMPTZ)
- **Soft Deletes**: `is_active` BOOLEAN (preferred over hard deletes)

### Key Entities
- `organizations` → `stations` → `tanks`, `nozzles`, `users`
- `organizations` → `subscriptions` → `subscription_payments`
- `refresh_tokens` (user_id → AspNetUsers; stores hashed tokens, ip_address, user_agent, device_id)
- `subscription_plans` (system-defined: starter, professional, enterprise)
- `shifts` → `meter_readings`, `dip_readings`
- `credit_customers` → `credit_transactions`
- `suppliers` → `supplier_transactions`

### Multi-Tenancy
- **Always** include `station_id` in queries (except Owner's consolidated view)
- Use EF Core query filters for automatic tenant isolation
- Owner can aggregate across all stations

---

## Business Rules

### Shift Management (SH-001 to SH-006)
- Only one shift open per station at a time
- Opening meter reading must be ≥ last closing reading
- Shift cannot close until all assigned nozzles have closing readings
- Shortage = Calculated Sales - (Cash + Credit + Card + Digital)
- Shortage added to nozzleman's balance due
- Excess logged but not deducted from balance

### Pricing (PR-001 to PR-005)
- Only one active price per fuel type per station
- Price changes require confirmation (type twice)
- Price changes trigger notification to all station users
- Sales during price change split by time, calculated at respective rates
- Customer special rates applied automatically on credit sales

### Inventory (INV-001 to INV-005)
- Stock = Opening Dip + Deliveries - Sales (calculated)
- Physical stock from closing dip reading
- Variance = Physical Stock - Calculated Stock
- Variance exceeding threshold triggers alert
- Short delivery alerts sent to Owner immediately

### Credit Management (CR-001 to CR-004)
- Credit sale blocked if customer at/above credit limit
- Partial payments reduce outstanding balance
- Customer balance = Sum(sales) - Sum(payments)
- Aging calculated from transaction date

### Audit (AUD-001 to AUD-005)
- All price changes logged with before/after values
- All user create/delete actions logged
- Manual stock adjustments logged with reason
- Credit entry deletions logged
- Audit logs never deleted (retention: owner-configurable)

### Registration (REG-001 to REG-004)
- Email must be unique across all organizations
- Registration creates Organization + Owner + Station + Trial subscription in one transaction
- New registrations start on 14-day trial with Professional plan features
- Phone number validated for Pakistani format (+92XXXXXXXXXX)

### Subscription & Billing (SUB-001 to SUB-010)
- Each organization has exactly one active subscription at a time
- Trial period is 14 days from registration date
- Trial gives Professional plan features (full product experience)
- When trial expires, account becomes read-only (can view, cannot create/edit)
- Payment verification is manual (admin approves bank transfer proof)
- Subscription activates only after payment is verified
- 3-day grace period after subscription expires before read-only mode
- Downgrade blocked if current usage exceeds target plan limits
- Annual billing gives ~17% discount (2 months free)
- Feature gating enforced at API level (not just UI)

### Feature Gating (FG-001 to FG-005)
- Station count checked on station creation against plan limits
- User count checked on user creation against plan limits
- Module access checked via plan's feature flags JSONB
- Expired/cancelled subscriptions allow read-only access
- Owner always sees upgrade prompts for gated features

