## Code Standards

### Frontend

**React Components**:
- Use functional components with hooks
- Extract custom hooks for reusable logic
- Colocate styles with components (Tailwind)
- Use TypeScript for all components
- Use Shadcn/ui components as base for UI elements
- Customize Shadcn components by modifying files in `components/ui/` (you own the code)

**State Management**:
- **TanStack Query**: All server state (API calls, caching)
- **Zustand**: Client-only state (theme, language, sidebar, UI state)
- **TanStack Form**: Form state and validation

**Forms**:
- Use TanStack Form + Zod validation
- Share Zod schemas with backend DTOs when possible
- Show validation errors inline

**API Calls**:
- Use TanStack Query hooks (`useQuery`, `useMutation`)
- Centralize API client in `lib/api.ts`
- Handle errors consistently (toast notifications)

**Routing**:
- File-based routing with TanStack Router
- Type-safe route params and search params
- Protected routes via route loaders

### Backend (Clean Architecture)

**Domain Layer** (`FuelFlow.Domain`):
- Entities are plain C# classes (POCOs) — no EF Core attributes
- Enums for strongly-typed values (UserRole, ShiftStatus, etc.)
- BaseEntity with common fields: Id (Guid), CreatedAt, UpdatedAt
- Zero external NuGet packages — if Domain needs a package, reconsider design

**Application Layer** (`FuelFlow.Application`):
- Define service interfaces (IAuthService, IShiftService, etc.)
- Define repository interfaces (IRepository<T>, IUnitOfWork)
- DTOs for all request/response objects
- FluentValidation validators for DTOs
- Result<T> type for service return values (success/failure without exceptions)

**Infrastructure Layer** (`FuelFlow.Infrastructure`):
- Implements interfaces from Application
- AppDbContext extends IdentityDbContext<AppUser, AppRole, Guid>
- EF Core Fluent API in Configurations/ folder (entity-per-file)
- Repository<T> implements IRepository<T>
- JWT token service, external integrations (SMS, S3)
- DependencyInjection.cs extension method to register all Infrastructure services

**Api Layer** (`FuelFlow.Api`):
- Keep controllers thin — send Commands/Queries via MediatR, no business logic
- Return DTOs, never entities directly
- Use `[Authorize]` attributes for auth
- Program.cs is the composition root (registers all DI)
- Middleware for global error handling (RFC 7807 Problem Details)
- Serilog for structured logging
- Swagger for API docs in development

**General Backend Rules**:
- Use async/await for all DB operations
- Apply EF Core query filters for multi-tenancy
- Use Mapperly for DTO ↔ Entity mapping (source-generated, in Infrastructure)
- Don't expose internal errors or stack traces to clients

