## UI/UX Guidelines

### Component Library
- **Shadcn/ui**: Base components (customizable, accessible)
  - Installed and configured in `components.json`
  - Add components via: `npx shadcn@latest add [component-name]`
  - Uses Radix UI primitives + class-variance-authority
  - Components stored in `src/components/ui/`
  - Example: `import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button'`
- **DataTable**: TanStack Table + Shadcn styling
- **Forms**: TanStack Form + Zod + Shadcn form components
- **Modals**: Dialog component for confirmations
- **Toasts**: Sonner for notifications (to be added)
- **Charts**: Recharts with consistent theme

### Responsive Design
- **Mobile**: < 640px (Nozzleman entry screens)
- **Tablet**: 640px - 1024px (Manager on tablet)
- **Desktop**: > 1024px (Full dashboard)

### Localization
- Support English and Urdu
- Use `react-i18next` for translations
- Store translations in `locales/en.json` and `locales/ur.json`
- Date format: DD/MM/YYYY
- Currency format: Rs. 1,25,000 (Pakistani notation)

### PWA Features
- Service worker caches app shell
- Add to home screen prompt
- Offline support for critical features

---

## Security & Permissions

### Roles
- **Owner**: Full access, create Managers, configure all settings
- **Manager**: Manage shifts, view reports, create other users
- **Custom Users**: Configurable granular permissions

### Permissions
- Granular per-module: View / Edit / Delete / No Access
- Manager can be assigned to multiple stations
- Owner sees consolidated "All Stations" dashboard

### Authentication
- JWT Bearer tokens
- Refresh token mechanism
- PIN-based quick login (optional)
- Session timeout configurable per user

### Authorization
- Check permissions at API level
- Filter data by station access at query level
- Owner bypasses station filters for consolidated views

---

## Testing Guidelines

### Frontend
- Test React components with React Testing Library
- Test hooks in isolation
- Mock TanStack Query in tests
- Test form validation with Zod schemas

### Backend (Clean Architecture Testing)
- **Domain**: Unit test entities and business rules (no mocking needed — pure C#)
- **Application**: Unit test service logic with mocked repository interfaces
- **Infrastructure**: Integration tests for EF Core, query filters, multi-tenancy
- **Api**: Integration tests for full API endpoints (WebApplicationFactory)

