## Common Patterns

### CQRS + MediatR
```csharp
// Controller - thin, only sends command/query
var result = await _mediator.Send(new LoginCommand(request));
if (!result.IsSuccess) return Unauthorized(new { error = result.Error });
return Ok(new { success = true, data = result.Data });

// Application - Command (IRequest<Result<T>>)
public record LoginCommand(LoginRequest Request) : IRequest<Result<AuthResponse>>;

// Application - Query
public record GetCurrentUserQuery(Guid UserId) : IRequest<Result<AuthResponse>>;

// Infrastructure - Handler implements IRequestHandler
public class LoginCommandHandler : IRequestHandler<LoginCommand, Result<AuthResponse>>
{
    public async Task<Result<AuthResponse>> Handle(LoginCommand request, CancellationToken ct)
    {
        // Business logic here
        return Result<AuthResponse>.Success(authResponse);
    }
}
```

### Refresh Token (DB-Backed, Rotation)
- Login/Register create refresh token, store hash in `refresh_tokens`, return plain token to client
- `POST /auth/refreshToken`: validate token, revoke old, create new, return new access + refresh tokens
- Session tracking: `IRequestContextService` provides `ClientIp`, `UserAgent`; optional `deviceId` from request body
- Handlers inject `IRefreshTokenRepository`, `IRequestContextService` for token persistence and metadata

### Password Reset (Token-Based)
- `POST /auth/forgot-password`: accepts email; sends reset link via IAuthService (generic success for security)
- `POST /auth/reset-password`: accepts `userId`, `token`, `newPassword`; UserManager.ResetPasswordAsync
- Token expiry: 24 hours (DataProtectionTokenProviderOptions in DependencyInjection)

### Multi-Tenant Queries
```csharp
// Backend - Always filter by StationId
var tanks = await _repository.GetAll()
    .Where(t => t.StationId == currentStationId)
    .ToListAsync();

// Owner can see all stations
if (user.Role == "owner")
{
    tanks = await _repository.GetAll().ToListAsync();
}
```

### API Error Handling
```typescript
// Frontend - Consistent error handling
try {
  const data = await api.post('/api/v1/shifts', payload);
  toast.success('Shift opened successfully');
} catch (error) {
  toast.error(error.response?.data?.detail || 'Failed to open shift');
}
```

### Feature Gating (Subscription)
```csharp
// Backend - Check plan limits before creating resources
var subscription = await _subscriptionService.GetActiveSubscription(orgId);
var plan = subscription.Plan;

// Check station limit
if (plan.MaxStations != -1)
{
    var stationCount = await _stationRepo.CountByOrgAsync(orgId);
    if (stationCount >= plan.MaxStations)
        return Result.Fail("Station limit reached. Upgrade your plan.");
}

// Check feature flag
if (!plan.Features.GetProperty("sms").GetBoolean())
    return Result.Fail("SMS not available on your plan. Upgrade to Professional.");
```

```typescript
// Frontend - Show upgrade prompt for gated features
const { data: subscription } = useSubscription();
const canExportReports = subscription?.plan.features.reports_export ?? false;

{canExportReports ? (
  <Button onClick={handleExport}>Export PDF</Button>
) : (
  <UpgradePrompt feature="Report Exports" />
)}
```

### Form Validation
```typescript
// Frontend - TanStack Form + Zod schema (shared with backend DTOs)
const shiftSchema = z.object({
  stationId: z.string().uuid(),
  shiftName: z.string().min(1),
  openingCash: z.number().min(0),
});
// Use useForm from @tanstack/react-form with zodValidator(shiftSchema)

// Backend - FluentValidation
public class CreateShiftValidator : AbstractValidator<CreateShiftDto>
{
    public CreateShiftValidator()
    {
        RuleFor(x => x.StationId).NotEmpty();
        RuleFor(x => x.ShiftName).NotEmpty();
        RuleFor(x => x.OpeningCash).GreaterThanOrEqualTo(0);
    }
}
```

